The industry body&#8217;s business confidence index increased to 93.9 in November. CAPE TOWN - The South African Chamber of Commerce and Industry (Sacci) says business confidence has improved by 0.9 index points recovering from the exceptionally low level in October.The industry body s business confidence index increased to 93.9 in November.The positive monthly contributors came from real value of building plans passed, new vehicle sales and manufacturing output.Sacci economist Richard Downing says: While the outlook is still negative, I think we are in positive territory due to business confidence. We must still remember that we re coming from a low level, especially from September. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)